  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: Lastest develop\nOS & Version: Linux\nCommit hash : N/A\n#### Expected behaviour\n\ngeth should return the actual value of the logsBloom field of the pending block from the eth.getBlock(\"pending\") call.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\ngeth returns null in the logsBloom field\n\nRationale:\nIn order to calculate the HashNoNonce() value of the pending block the logsBloom field is required and is currently not provided by the RPC call. Without this value it is impossible for an external miner to check if the hash he is currently mining on really corresponds to a given block (prove of honesty during mining).\n",
