    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It can be used by miners to check the honesty of the pool. The pool provides the block hash and the corresponding pending block (which includes the pools coinbase address). The miners can then independently calculate the HashNoNonce from the given pending block and compare it to the block hash they are mining on.\n\nIn my opinion eth.getBlock(\"pending\") should return the same information that is used to calculate the HashNoNonce value and not arbitrarily null some fields if they are used internally.\n",
